  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Application Developer",
  "description": "<p>As a <strong>Custom Software Engineer</strong>, you will design, build, and enhance <strong>custom software solutions</strong> across systems and applications to address complex business needs. You will leverage <strong>modern frameworks, low-code platforms, and agile delivery practices</strong> to deliver <strong>scalable, high-performance solutions</strong>.</p><p>You are expected to work <strong>independently</strong>, take ownership of deliverables, and develop into a <strong>subject matter expert</strong>. Active participation in team discussions is essential, along with contributing innovative solutions to technical and delivery challenges.</p><p><strong>Key Responsibilities</strong></p><ul><li><p>Collaborate with cross-functional stakeholders to gather requirements and translate them into clear technical designs and specifications.</p></li><li><p>Design, develop, and implement custom applications using <strong>OutSystems</strong>, adhering to industry and Accenture best practices.</p></li><li><p>Ensure high-quality, secure, and maintainable code through strong software engineering and design principles.</p></li><li><p>Continuously assess and enhance existing applications to improve performance, scalability, and user experience.</p></li><li><p>Mentor junior team members and contribute to a collaborative, knowledge-sharing team culture.</p></li><li><p>Stay current with emerging technologies and industry trends to drive innovation and improve project outcomes.</p></li></ul><p><strong>Skills & Qualifications</strong></p><ul><li><p><strong>Expert proficiency in OutSystems</strong>.</p></li><li><p><strong>Advanced proficiency in Custom Application Development</strong> (preferred).</p></li><li><p>Strong expertise in <strong>Software Design & Solutions</strong> and <strong>Software Engineering</strong>.</p></li><li><p>Experience working in <strong>agile delivery environments</strong> with cross-functional teams.</p></li></ul>",
